Description: Frustrated to find that the office chair you sit on for years start sagging or can’t go up and down anymore? But not ready to buy a new one because the rest of the chair is in perfect shape? Why not get to fix it by changing the gas lift cylinder by yourself? How to make sure the gas lift cylinder fits your office chair? Check the outer and inner diameter of your broken gas lift cylinder. This replacement part fits the one with an outer diameter of 2" and inner diameter of 1.1". How to install the gas lift cylinder on your own? Tip the chair onto its side.Use the rubber mallet to tap and remove the base of the chair away from the seat.Use the pipe wrench to clamp tightly onto the top of the cylinder. Twist and then pull up in order to remove the cylinder.Remove the orange cap of the new cylinder. Insert the bottom of the cylinder into the center of the chair base.Carefully lift both the chair base and the chair cylinder into the chair mechanism. The parts will then fasten on their own. Specifications: Material: SteelOuter Cylinder Diameter: 2" - Inner Cylinder Diameter: 1.1" - Stroke: 5.5" - Bearing Capacity: 1000 lbs Package Content: 1 Office Chair Gas Lift Cylinder

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install
reviews.reviewText: This is the third cylinder that I have replaced on my home office chair. This gas lift cylinder seems to be more robust and better suited for my chair. As normal, no installation instructions were included, but I have done this before, so it was pretty straight forward. I have had no issues with its functioning.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Staples chair stock cylinder was too short for an ergonomically correct height. This many more inches and now makes the chair perfectly usable. Fit perfectly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Need a removal tool to use this
reviews.reviewText: This cylinder installs well and works as designed. However, it does not come with a tool to remove the existing cylinder so you can install this one. If you have a pipe wrench you can use that, but if you're like me and don't have one you'll either need to buy a pipe wrench or buy a specialty tool for the purpose. You can get an equally strong cylinder with the removal tool for the cost of this cylinder and a separate pipe wrench, and for less if you buy this cylinder and the specialty tool separately. I'd recommend saving yourself some effort by buying an all-in-one kit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars First one sank to the bottom, 2nd one is good
reviews.reviewText: Obviously you are the practical type if you are thinking about buying this. The think is, you need to be able to get the old shaft and cylinder off. Don't believe the manufacturer's movie, it's a joke! I have a good solid metal vice and was able to separate the tapered connections on each end using hammer blows and some wood to protect the chair. Relatively easy but it takes a little man handling (am I still allowed to say that?). What was really a problem for me was the first one I got sank to the bottom. There was also fluid leaking around the seal. However, it was no problem because I was able to get a replacement which works perfectly fine. It was just a bit more labor to take off the bad one and put the replacement on. This was actually an upgrade from the original because I got a longer shaft. Now I can sit higher up now which i prefer. It still goes down far enough when you need it to. This fixed a nice $400 chair that I was given, so I'm happy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars 180 day warranty is accurate.
reviews.reviewText: Purchased because they said 1000 pound limit. I am not even close to a third of that weight, but after the warranty date, but not by much it failed. when not in the chair, it rises to the highest setting and when you sit in it it sinks to the lowest setting. Lucky I can handle sitting at the height when I use this item. Would love a recommendation on a quality product that can last for a couple of years.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Lifesaving purchase for me. My chair is a good chair but the hydraulic in it was failing. I got this as a replacement and its a world of difference not having to raise yourself every 5 minutes.This 5.5 inch one however is taller than your normal office chair hydraulic so keep that in mind maybe go with the next one down for office chairs but mine still works great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Repaired and sitting pretty
reviews.reviewText: Other than removing the old cylinder from the chair, this repair was easy. My fault, because I have tall wheels the length is just slightly taller than I anticipated. Excellent product and I would purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Does not hold up to Everyday use.
reviews.reviewText: I originally bought this 1 1/2 years ago and about a Month ago it started dropping down to the bottom. I have always liked it at the highest level. Since I don't weigh anywhere near 1000 pounds (280 lbs) I have to give it a thumbs down for lasting very long. So I suggest you take the heavy duty claims with a grain of salt. Having said that, A 20 dollar replacement is still a lot better than buying a new 2 to 3 hundred dollar chair which is what I used to do. My actual chair is still in great shape material wise so even though it's not the best solution, I still ordered another one yesterday to replace the failing one.
